1)Components Of Kubernetes✔
Ans)𝗞𝘂𝗯𝗲𝗿𝗻𝗲𝘁𝗲𝘀 𝗖𝗼𝗺𝗽𝗼𝗻𝗲𝗻𝘁𝘀: Pod, Ingress, Service, ConfigMap, Secrets, Volumes

𝗣𝗼𝗱𝘀: The basic unit of deployment, comprising one or more containers that work together.

𝗜𝗻𝗴𝗿𝗲𝘀𝘀: Manages external access to the services in a Kubernetes cluster.

𝗦𝗲𝗿𝘃𝗶𝗰𝗲: Acts as an abstraction layer to expose pods, ensuring seamless communication.

𝗖𝗼𝗻𝗳𝗶𝗴𝗠𝗮𝗽: A way to store configuration information in key-value pairs.

𝗦𝗲𝗰𝗿𝗲𝘁𝘀: Securely manage sensitive information like passwords or API keys.

𝗩𝗼𝗹𝘂𝗺𝗲𝘀: Enables data persistence, allowing containers to share and store data.

🏗️ 𝗞𝘂𝗯𝗲𝗿𝗻𝗲𝘁𝗲𝘀 𝗔𝗿𝗰𝗵𝗶𝘁𝗲𝗰𝘁𝘂𝗿𝗲: 𝗠𝗮𝘀𝘁𝗲𝗿 𝗡𝗼𝗱𝗲 𝘃𝘀. 𝗪𝗼𝗿𝗸𝗲𝗿 𝗡𝗼𝗱𝗲

𝗠𝗮𝘀𝘁𝗲𝗿 𝗡𝗼𝗱𝗲:
𝗔𝗣𝗜 𝗦𝗲𝗿𝘃𝗲𝗿: Serves the Kubernetes API and is the entry point for all REST commands.
𝗦𝗰𝗵𝗲𝗱𝘂𝗹𝗲𝗿: Assigns work (pods) to nodes based on resource availability and constraints.
𝗖𝗼𝗻𝘁𝗿𝗼𝗹𝗹𝗲𝗿 𝗠𝗮𝗻𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗿: Maintains the desired state of the system via controllers.
𝗲𝘁𝗰𝗱: Consistent and highly-available key-value store for all cluster data.

𝗪𝗼𝗿𝗸𝗲𝗿 𝗡𝗼𝗱𝗲:
𝗞𝘂𝗯𝗲𝗹𝗲𝘁: Ensures that containers are running in a Pod.
𝗞𝘂𝗯𝗲 𝗣𝗿𝗼𝘅𝘆: Maintains network rules on nodes and performs simple TCP/UDP stream forwarding.
𝗖𝗼𝗻𝘁𝗮𝗶𝗻𝗲𝗿 𝗥𝘂𝗻𝘁𝗶𝗺𝗲: Software responsible for running containers.







